  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at national and international levels:\n\n1. International frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National regulations:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs)\n\n3. Key compliance measures:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Establishing audit trails\n- Implementing strict financial controls\n\n4. Penalties for non-compliance:\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Potential business license revocation\n\n5. Jurisdictional approaches:\n- Different countries have varying levels of stringency\n- Increasing global cooperation and information sharing\n- Harmonizing international standards\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent criminal organizations from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income.",
